Sure! Below is a Java program that downloads an image from a URL, applies a basic filter (such as a grayscale filter), and saves the modified image to disk.

This program uses the `java.net` package to download the image, the `javax.imageio` package to read and write images, and the `java.awt.image` package to apply a grayscale filter.

```java
import java.awt.image.BufferedImage;
import java.awt.image.GrayscaleFilter;
import java.io.*;
import java.net.URL;
import javax.imageio.ImageIO;

public class ImageFilterDownloader {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String imageUrl = "https://example.com/image.jpg"; // Replace with your image URL
        String outputFilePath = "filtered_image.jpg";

        try {
            // Download the image from the URL
            BufferedImage originalImage = downloadImageFromURL(imageUrl);
            if (originalImage == null) {
                System.out.println("Failed to download the image.");
                return;
            }

            // Apply a grayscale filter
            BufferedImage filteredImage = applyGrayscaleFilter(originalImage);

            // Save the filtered image to disk
            saveImageToFile(filteredImage, outputFilePath);

            System.out.println("Image downloaded, filtered, and saved to: " + outputFilePath);

        } catch (Exception e) {
            System.err.println("An error occurred: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    private static BufferedImage downloadImageFromURL(String imageUrl) throws IOException {
        URL url = new URL(imageUrl);
        BufferedImage image = ImageIO.read(url.openStream());
        return image;
    }

    private static BufferedImage applyGrayscaleFilter(BufferedImage image) {
        BufferedImage filtered = (BufferedImage) image.getGraphics().createGraphics();
        filtered = new BufferedImage(image.getWidth(), image.getHeight(), BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_RGB);
        Graphics2D g2d = (Graphics2D) filtered.getGraphics();
        g2d.drawImage(image, 0, 0, null);
        g2d.dispose();

        // Apply grayscale filter
        GrayscaleFilter filter = new GrayscaleFilter();
        filter.filter(g2d, filtered);
        return filtered;
    }

    private static void saveImageToFile(BufferedImage image, String outputPath) throws IOException {
        ImageIO.write(image, "jpg", new File(outputPath));
    }
}
```

### Explanation:

- **`downloadImageFromURL`**: Downloads the image from the specified URL and returns it as a `BufferedImage`.
- **`applyGrayscaleFilter`**: Applies a grayscale filter to the image using the `GrayscaleFilter` class.
- **`saveImageToFile`**: Saves the filtered image to the specified file path in JPEG format.

### Notes:

- Replace `"https://example.com/image.jpg"` with the actual URL of the image you want to process.
- Ensure that the file path (`filtered_image.jpg`) is valid and writable by the current user.

